<br>
A mage-only Fear raid.  Well, not entirely mage-only: we'd need a cleric or two for rezzes and (preferably) a monk with lots of SoW potions to pull.  But the idea would be, NO ENCHANTERS, NO TANKS.<br>
<br>
I've been thinking about the mechanics of this; with no enchanters, it means no crowd control.  If you have 30 mages in the Plane of Fear, all with pets, I think it's pretty likely that even if you were to bring 5 mobs on a bad pull, having an average of 6 pets per mob (plus chain-casting!), you'd have a lot of dead mobs in no time flat.<br>
<br>
Breaking the plane is the same as any other raid: Everyone runs in and camps at the north wall, then comes back once the camp is clear.  The cleric does rezzes, and then the monk goes and starts pulling.  Preferably one mob at a time.<br>
<br>
In a one-mob scenario, you have (roughly) 30 pets beating on the mob at once.  Even if a pet only does, say, 50 damage every 2 seconds, that's 750 damage per second.  Mobs in Fear have around 14,000hp, which means mobs last about 18 seconds each.  Since the pets would all be doing roughly the same melee damage, no one pet would be the focus of the mob's attack, and it's entirely possible that no pets would die before the mob did.  And we all know that our pets at 49 do far more than 25 damage per second -- especially with Burnout III.  If your pets are doing 50 damage per second -- which is STILL less than they really do! -- then a Fear mob will last, on average, NINE SECONDS.  Think about the times you've been to Fear.  Does any mob die in 9 seconds?  Never.<br>
<br>
After the battle, pets regenerate so fast that you'd likely have 30 full-strength pets before the next pull.  Even if you didn't, only some of the pets would even have taken damage during the fight; if they weren't all to full at the next fight, the weakened pets could be held off a few seconds, to reduce the chance of them getting beat on more by the new mobs.<br>
<br>
Then there's the situation of, what happens when 5 mobs get pulled?  It's hard to coordinate an exact right number of pets per mob, so you'd probably just have people target whatever is nearby and send their pet after it.  Hopefully people would try to distribute their pets evenly.  Or maybe it wouldn't even matter; maybe the mobs would die so fast, you could just redirect your pets every 10-20 seconds and beat all the mobs into paste.<br>
<br>
All of this assumes, of course, no nuking, and that the mages chain-summon their pets when they die.  Nuking is ineffective against many mobs in Fear -- like Amygdalan warriors and knights -- but melee damage works just fine.<br>
<br>
Everyone would probably want to bring an entire backpack full of stacks of Malachite, and another important thing would be to have everyone have their Earthen Boots, so that on the off chance that your pet gets feared and runs off, you can suicide it instantly.<br>
<br>
To me, this sounds like a workable idea, and I'd like to try to get at least 30 of the level 49+ mages on The Nameless to participate.<br>
<br>
Ideas?  Suggestions?  I'd really like to do this, which means reserving a Fear date for a month or two from now, and making sure that we really can get 30 mages together to do this thing.<br>
